    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/614094b8f22ed98e516b858b4b84f163?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 7577842,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5749570,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5749570/vhs",
                "reputation": 10228,
                "display_name": "VHS"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1489548947,
            "creation_date": 1489548947,
            "body": "<p>How about the following way?<\/p>\n\n<p><code>x = x.substring(0, x.length() - 1) + \".\" + x.substring(x.length() - 1);<\/code><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 42800656,
            "question_id": 42800554
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/z21Fe.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 386394,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 744133,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/744133/yoyo",
                "reputation": 9495,
                "display_name": "YoYo",
                "accept_rate": 57
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1489609081,
            "creation_date": 1489550133,
            "body": "<p>If your concern is the internal rounding that happens with a float representation, consider using <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/math/BigDecimal.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>BigDecimal<\/code><\/a>. Like:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>BigDecimal v = BigDecimal.valueOf(500,1);\nSystem.out.println(v.toString());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>or combined as <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(BigDecimal.valueOf(500,1).toString());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>or maybe you need to use <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(BigDecimal.valueOf(500,1).toPlainString());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>And to answer your original question directly, even this works:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>BigDecimal v11 = BigDecimal.valueOf(mArray[18] &amp; 0xFF | mArray[19] &lt;&lt; 8,1);\ndata11.put(\"Text2\", String.format(\"%.1f\", v11));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>But the real question is if this is all really needed or not.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 42800823,
            "question_id": 42800554,
            "last_edit_date": 1489609081
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d10432298a6eacf6be2f263d8fc3776b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2375630,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2815219,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2815219/raman-sahasi",
                "reputation": 32061,
                "display_name": "Raman Sahasi"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1489549133,
            "creation_date": 1489549133,
            "body": "<p>How about this?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(500*0.1);\nSystem.out.println(491*0.1);\nSystem.out.println(455*0.1);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Output<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>50.0                                                                                                                                                                                                  \n49.1                                                                                                                                                                                                  \n45.5 \n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 42800681,
            "question_id": 42800554
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/kKvXH.gif?s=256",
                "account_id": 31180,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 85421,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/85421/user85421",
                "reputation": 29752,
                "display_name": "user85421"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1489557496,
            "creation_date": 1489557496,
            "body": "<p>I would go by integer division and modulo: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private static String format(int value) {\n    return (value / 10) + \".\" + Math.abs(value % 10);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><code>Math.abs()<\/code> can be removed if not using negative numbers:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private static String format(int value) {\n    return (value / 10) + \".\" + (value % 10);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><em>Obviously the method can be inlined...<\/em><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 42802090,
            "question_id": 42800554
        }
    ],
